1
00:00:04,670 --> 00:00:05,830
Tak Sungwoong.

2
00:00:06,690 --> 00:00:08,800
That's the man Jahyeon loves most.

3
00:00:10,150 --> 00:00:12,430
A lover she couldn't forget

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:15,540
even if she died.

5
00:00:16,210 --> 00:00:19,010
A lover she couldn't forget
even if she killed him.

6
00:00:21,790 --> 00:00:24,180
Could he have killed him for Oh Jahyeon?

7
00:00:24,340 --> 00:00:25,100
No.

8
00:00:26,590 --> 00:00:30,600
Rather than saying Koryoin Kim died
because the drug bag in his stomach burst

9
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:33,260
was intentional,
it's more like a coincidence.

10
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:36,070
But why was his body dumped?

11
00:00:36,770 --> 00:00:40,170
Could it be because they
mistakenly thought they killed him?

12
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:42,780
But,

13
00:00:43,620 --> 00:00:47,590
why on earth would Director Tak
help Oh Jahyeon?

14
00:00:48,110 --> 00:00:50,110
Didn't she say they love each other?

15
00:00:50,350 --> 00:00:52,130
Can you understand it just based on that,

16
00:00:52,130 --> 00:00:53,300
Prosecutor Ju?

17
00:00:54,070 --> 00:00:55,690
Don't try to understand it.

18
00:00:56,310 --> 00:00:58,970
The harder you think,
the less you'll understand.

19
00:00:58,970 --> 00:01:01,980
Love is inherently
ignorant and irrational.

20
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:08,480
Fasten your seatbelt. Let's go.

21
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:09,710
Where to?

22
00:01:11,789 --> 00:01:13,050
To find Tak Sungwoong.

23
00:01:13,350 --> 00:01:16,020
[Prosecutors' Office]

24
00:01:16,289 --> 00:01:19,039
[Room 703]

25
00:01:19,039 --> 00:01:20,340
[Chief Prosecutor Tak Sungwoong, Room 703]

26
00:01:20,730 --> 00:01:22,690
Director Tak, I'm Ju Taeseon.

27
00:01:22,930 --> 00:01:24,550
Come in.

28
00:01:29,060 --> 00:01:31,150
I was just about to call you.

29
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:33,580
That Supervisor Lee Chaeha...

30
00:01:34,150 --> 00:01:36,930
what do you think about transferring him
to a different department?

31
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:39,729
Having Lee Gilyoung's son
investigate Oh Jahyeon

32
00:01:39,940 --> 00:01:41,289
makes me feel uneasy.

33
00:01:42,690 --> 00:01:43,470
Oh?

34
00:01:43,660 --> 00:01:45,700
Ah, hello.

35
00:01:45,990 --> 00:01:47,470
Why are you here?

36
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,430
W-Well...

37
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:52,300
What are you doing?

38
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:04,020
I... I just wanted to drink some water.

39
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:09,120
Prosecutor Ju and I went out
for fieldwork and I suddenly got thirsty.

40
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,130
I used this cup...

41
00:02:13,610 --> 00:02:14,850
It's fine.

42
00:02:15,010 --> 00:02:17,740
I grew up in an environment
without so many rules.

43
00:02:20,130 --> 00:02:21,890
The water here tastes better.

44
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,810
I'll be going now.

45
00:02:26,410 --> 00:02:28,530
Goodbye. Please go ahead.

46
00:02:43,579 --> 00:02:45,770
[Park Siwoo]

47
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:50,560
[Kim Yunsik]

48
00:02:55,820 --> 00:02:57,579
[Kwak Seunghwan]
[Because of inheritance?]

49
00:02:58,130 --> 00:02:59,800
[Koryoin Mr. Kim overdosed on drugs]

50
00:03:00,070 --> 00:03:01,680
[Found in a small room
on the second floor]

51
00:03:01,910 --> 00:03:03,960
[The Last Abandoned Mine in Danhyeon City
To Be Turned Into a Casino]

52
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:06,700
[Led by Ohsong Construction, 'Danhyeon Land' Integrated Resort (Casino, Hotel, Theme Park) to be built—
Officially secures $400M in foreign investment]

53
00:03:06,890 --> 00:03:11,370
[Casino Industry's First Female Executive…
Pledges "Transparent Operations, Regional Co-Prosperity"]

54
00:03:11,450 --> 00:03:13,040
[Danhyeon City "Casino Owner Murdered";
the suspect is his driver, Lee]

55
00:03:19,579 --> 00:03:21,950
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

56
00:03:21,990 --> 00:03:25,000
[Prosecutor's Office]

57
00:03:30,230 --> 00:03:31,160
What's going on?

58
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,100
Haven't gotten off work yet?

59
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:34,360
Where's the paper cup?

60
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,560
I've already passed it
to the National Forensic Service

61
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,850
and asked them to compare it
with the DNA in the glove.

62
00:03:38,850 --> 00:03:40,880
You told them to contact you
as soon as the results are out, right?

63
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,810
Yes.

64
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:45,180
Prosecutor Ju.

65
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:50,360
You hope it isn't Director Tak, right?

66
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:57,400
I completely understand how you feel.

67
00:03:58,570 --> 00:03:59,980
Don't make wild guesses,

68
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:02,450
and don't project yourself onto me.

69
00:04:02,630 --> 00:04:05,450
Even if you stop the investigation here,
no one will blame you.

70
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:06,760
I won't stop.

71
00:04:08,820 --> 00:04:09,930
Why?

72
00:04:10,380 --> 00:04:13,380
You have nothing to do with any of the cases.

73
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,670
No matter what the final result is,

74
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,519
you will lose Director Tak.

75
00:04:20,899 --> 00:04:22,460
It's for the truth.

76
00:04:23,300 --> 00:04:25,640
I'm afraid that if you started this
because of me,

77
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:27,680
it will end up hurting you.

78
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:29,770
I'm worried.

79
00:04:30,820 --> 00:04:32,340
So what if you're worried?

80
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:34,040
What are you going to do?

81
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,550
You're just an investigator,
not a prosecutor.

82
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:39,150
How do you plan
to investigate this case alone?

83
00:04:39,150 --> 00:04:42,130
And I'm not doing this because of you.
Don't get the wrong idea.

84
00:04:42,130 --> 00:04:45,060
Doubt everything and uncover the truth—

85
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:46,920
that's what a prosecutor does.

86
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:51,280
So don't be arrogant and boss me around.

87
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:52,900
I'm sorry.

88
00:05:02,110 --> 00:05:02,960
Mr. Lee!

89
00:05:03,210 --> 00:05:04,160
Mr. Lee.

90
00:05:08,090 --> 00:05:09,410
I'm late, aren't I?

91
00:05:09,680 --> 00:05:10,550
Sorry.

92
00:05:10,660 --> 00:05:13,210
No, I just got here too.

93
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:16,510
Sorry for taking up your weekend.

94
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:19,370
I just thought you might be busy
with work all weekend.

95
00:05:19,370 --> 00:05:21,460
You and Prosecutor Ju
have been super busy lately.

96
00:05:21,460 --> 00:05:22,710
And you're often out in the field.

97
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:24,170
It's pretty much the same.

98
00:05:24,530 --> 00:05:27,010
People like Oh Jahyeon
should face their doom.

99
00:05:27,010 --> 00:05:27,910
What?

100
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:30,670
She's making you super tired.

101
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:33,740
Indeed.

102
00:05:34,010 --> 00:05:35,690
By the way, where are we going?

103
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:39,050
Follow me.

104
00:05:43,620 --> 00:05:45,880
We still have some time before the movie.

105
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:48,700
This is the best place to relieve stress.

106
00:05:50,110 --> 00:05:51,260
Give me your phone.

107
00:05:51,590 --> 00:05:52,250
Huh?

108
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:53,430
Hurry up.

109
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:56,960
[Slide to power off]

110
00:05:57,030 --> 00:05:57,800
Oh?

111
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:00,970
Don't think about work today.

112
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,390
Just have fun.

113
00:06:02,830 --> 00:06:03,680
Here.

114
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:05,560
Let's go!

115
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:10,240
Here I come.

116
00:06:14,150 --> 00:06:15,460
Please.

117
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:25,890
You can do it.

118
00:06:35,390 --> 00:06:36,190
Isn't it cute?

119
00:06:36,220 --> 00:06:37,290
Yeah, so cute.

120
00:06:37,450 --> 00:06:38,400
Here.

121
00:06:40,550 --> 00:06:41,550
Do you want to try?

122
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:11,770
Why did it suddenly start raining?

123
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,280
I know, right?

124
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:18,730
-Let's go.
-Yeah.

125
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:21,060
It's so cold.

126
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:28,400
The doors are closing.

127
00:07:32,180 --> 00:07:34,090
Do you want to have dinner
before you leave?

128
00:07:34,090 --> 00:07:35,630
I'm a good cook.

129
00:07:36,159 --> 00:07:37,700
After all,
I've lived alone for a long time.

130
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:40,390
[I'm worried. Did something happen?]
[I always feel like I'm causing bad things to happen to you,
and it makes me very anxious.]

131
00:07:37,909 --> 00:07:40,350
I'm worried. Did something happen?

132
00:07:42,090 --> 00:07:44,310
A-Ah, let's eat next time.

133
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,420
I'm afraid I have to go back first.

134
00:07:46,540 --> 00:07:47,250
Okay.

135
00:07:51,270 --> 00:07:53,260
Got it. See you on Monday.

136
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:55,060
The doors are closing.

137
00:08:06,090 --> 00:08:07,750
Seems like you had a good time.

138
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:09,570
Were you waiting for me?

139
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:11,590
Why didn't you answer the phone?

140
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,590
I was with Mr. Song.

141
00:08:13,710 --> 00:08:16,040
Did he stop you from answering my calls?

142
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:17,250
Well, not really.

143
00:08:17,380 --> 00:08:18,380
Then what was it?

144
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:21,000
Did you do something
I shouldn't catch you doing?

145
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:22,400
No.

146
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:25,820
We just went to the arcade.

147
00:08:27,870 --> 00:08:28,900
Is that so?

148
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:30,830
Go back and rest.

149
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,380
Huh?

150
00:08:35,380 --> 00:08:37,330
Aren't you going in with me?

151
00:08:38,169 --> 00:08:39,309
Let go of me.

152
00:08:41,650 --> 00:08:44,650
This hand that was just waving happily
at another man—

153
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:46,830
I don't want it holding me.

154
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,290
I'm leaving.

155
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,790
I'm afraid if we talk more,

156
00:08:56,790 --> 00:09:00,150
all the happiness you are feeling
will vanish.

157
00:09:00,570 --> 00:09:02,740
No, it won't...

158
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:09,490
Look at you. Your face is frozen.

159
00:09:12,970 --> 00:09:14,130
I'm leaving.

160
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,980
I've wasted enough time.

161
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:36,680
Mr. Lee, you're not in your dorm.

162
00:09:34,580 --> 00:09:39,760
[Mr. Lee, you're not in your dorm.
Why aren't you answering?
Contact me when you see this.]

163
00:09:36,890 --> 00:09:38,420
Why aren't you answering the phone?

164
00:09:38,420 --> 00:09:40,020
Contact me when you see this.

165
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:43,690
[02:12 Missed Call 02:25 Missed Call 02:38 Missed Call
02:38 Missed Call 02:50 Missed Call 02:50 Missed Call...]

166
00:09:43,780 --> 00:09:46,800
I always feel like I'm causing bad things to happen to you,
and it makes me very anxious.

167
00:09:43,780 --> 00:09:48,020
[I always feel like I'm causing bad things to happen to you,
and it makes me very anxious.]

168
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,460
It makes me feel very uneasy.

169
00:09:49,050 --> 00:09:50,540
I'm waiting at your door.

170
00:09:49,050 --> 00:09:53,010
[I'm waiting at your door.
Please answer the phone. Please.]

171
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:53,010
Please answer the phone. Please.

172
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:56,810
Did he wait for me for 3 hours?

173
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,320
I'm leaving.

174
00:10:03,530 --> 00:10:05,390
I've wasted enough time already.

175
00:10:36,450 --> 00:10:38,660
I told you to go.
Why follow me here?

176
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,640
If I had known you were coming,

177
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:43,830
I wouldn't have gone out with Mr. Song.

178
00:10:43,830 --> 00:10:47,080
Did you follow me here just to say this?

179
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:50,480
I'm not interested in the fun
you share with Mr. Song,

180
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,670
so just leave.

181
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:53,170
I don't want to.

182
00:10:58,020 --> 00:10:59,540
My patience today

183
00:11:00,430 --> 00:11:02,960
was already exhausted
while waiting for you.

184
00:11:02,980 --> 00:11:06,650
When I found out you were
having fun with Mr. Song,

185
00:11:06,780 --> 00:11:09,110
I even used up tomorrow's patience quota.

186
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:11,610
I'm much less patient
than usual right now.

187
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,390
So get lost.

188
00:11:16,570 --> 00:11:17,570
Prosecutor Ju.

189
00:11:21,410 --> 00:11:24,270
We didn't have any official business
to meet today.

190
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:27,990
Why on earth did I go to your place?

191
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:39,970
I'd love to tell you
I don't know why I did that,

192
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:49,810
but actually, I do know the reason.

193
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:53,720
As for you,

194
00:11:54,770 --> 00:11:56,810
do you know why you came here?

195
00:11:58,510 --> 00:12:01,900
Yes, I do.

196
00:12:03,290 --> 00:12:05,620
You have to hold back
like you normally do,

197
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,590
especially today.

198
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:15,300
If you want to leave,
turn around and go now.

199
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:16,950
I told you, didn't I?

200
00:12:17,280 --> 00:12:19,240
I have run out of patience today.

201
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:16,520
I don't plan on being gentle
with you today.

202
00:14:19,070 --> 00:14:20,520
Dry my hair properly.

203
00:14:21,820 --> 00:14:24,280
Are you really bossing me around
to dry your hair?

204
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:27,470
Are you jealous because
I went on a date with Mr. Song?

205
00:14:27,970 --> 00:14:31,020
Lee Chaeha, let's get things straight.

206
00:14:31,260 --> 00:14:32,370
Sorry.

207
00:14:32,610 --> 00:14:34,230
You are not jealous.

208
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,590
Date?

209
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:37,290
Are you two dating?

210
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:39,040
Uh, no.

211
00:15:07,810 --> 00:15:10,200
Do you have trouble sleeping too?

212
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:13,480
Yeah.

213
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:18,880
More often than not, I still can't sleep
even after taking medicine.

214
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,340
Prosecutor Ju,

215
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:43,380
are you upset about Director Tak?

216
00:15:44,570 --> 00:15:45,650
No.

217
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,820
I actually feel more at ease.

218
00:15:49,210 --> 00:15:50,090
What?

219
00:15:51,410 --> 00:15:52,950
S-Sorry.

220
00:15:53,510 --> 00:15:54,720
Turn your head away,

221
00:15:55,140 --> 00:15:56,880
before I turn around.

222
00:16:06,060 --> 00:16:08,520
Wasn't he like a father to you?

223
00:16:09,390 --> 00:16:12,280
And such a person became a murder suspect.

224
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:17,200
I suddenly had this thought.

225
00:16:19,170 --> 00:16:25,980
Maybe Lee Gilyoung...
isn't the real killer.

226
00:16:27,990 --> 00:16:29,350
Thoughts like this...

227
00:16:55,410 --> 00:16:56,470
Prosecutor!

228
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,100
Prosecutor!

229
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:07,280
What is all this?

230
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,800
I'm organizing the case.

231
00:17:14,010 --> 00:17:15,910
[Gambling addiction] [An intersection with the perpetrator] [Probability of an accomplice?]
[Why Danhyeon City?] [A client who pays well?]

232
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,170
[Oh Jahyeon's husband, Kwak Seunghwan] [Died 19.10.16]
[No way to prove the suspicion]

233
00:17:17,599 --> 00:17:20,660
The death of Oh Jahyeon's husband—
the cause of death is

234
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,520
a heart attack.

235
00:17:21,569 --> 00:17:22,960
[Heart attack. No external trauma. No drugs detected in the autopsy performed 12 hours later.
Cremation took place right after. Because of property division?]

236
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:25,589
Did Oh Jahyeon's husband die?

237
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:26,589
Yeah.

238
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:27,859
He had no external injuries

239
00:17:27,859 --> 00:17:29,350
and had no drugs detected.

240
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:32,360
[Autopsy performed after 12 hours]

241
00:17:30,860 --> 00:17:34,060
The autopsy was conducted
12 hours after death.

242
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:37,490
Very clean, right?

243
00:17:39,020 --> 00:17:42,880
That was the first thing Oh Jahyeon said
after the inspection. And...

244
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:46,510
[Oh Jahyeon's regular OB-GYN]
[Died 19.10.19]

245
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:47,260
What happened 3 days later was...

246
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:51,960
The murder of Granny Park with an awl.

247
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:53,900
Ransacking marks were deliberately made,

248
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:55,580
and it was an overkill with 20 stabs—

249
00:17:55,580 --> 00:17:56,820
a vendetta.

250
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:01,770
[A change in the murder weapon?]

251
00:17:59,390 --> 00:18:01,460
A change in the murder weapon?

252
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:04,510
The culprit confessed, didn't they?

253
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:07,630
It's exactly the same.

254
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:10,280
I'm here to turn myself in.

255
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:13,930
In these two cases,
the suspects' former occupations were...

256
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:15,500
[Granny Park's case: surrendered suspect]

257
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:18,030
[Koryoin Kim's case: surrendered suspect]

258
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:18,070
When I was young...

259
00:18:18,390 --> 00:18:20,500
I was a retired miner.

260
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:22,240
Both miners.

261
00:18:23,670 --> 00:18:24,600
[Koryoin Kim]

262
00:18:23,810 --> 00:18:26,340
The case of Koryoin Kim's dumped body.

263
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,180
[Cause of death: meth overdose,
excess nicotine detected, drug dealer]

264
00:18:26,180 --> 00:18:27,410
[Needle marks found on neck and arms]

265
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:30,500
The cause of death was a meth overdose.

266
00:18:30,740 --> 00:18:34,590
Needle marks on the neck,
and excess nicotine was detected.

267
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:37,440
And a glove dropped at the scene.

268
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:40,080
He didn't even return the room key.

269
00:18:40,690 --> 00:18:42,150
When I saw him leaving
with a suitcase that day,

270
00:18:42,150 --> 00:18:43,810
I should have known.

271
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:47,660
His whereabouts after
he entered the country couldn't be traced.

272
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:48,980
Now we

273
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:54,280
agree that the Koryoin died
while smuggling drugs with his body.

274
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:57,050
Then in your opinion,

275
00:18:57,180 --> 00:19:00,160
where in Danhyeon City could you buy

276
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:02,040
such a large amount of drugs?

277
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:04,690
Casino World.

278
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,630
Do you know where most people
from miner families in Danhyeon City

279
00:19:07,630 --> 00:19:09,690
work?

280
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:11,650
It's Casino World.

281
00:19:11,830 --> 00:19:16,260
That's exactly why the Coal Mining Association
brought in the casino in the first place.

282
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:17,520
Do you see it now?

283
00:19:19,190 --> 00:19:20,830
The connection

284
00:19:22,680 --> 00:19:24,100
between all the cases.

285
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:29,270
[Oh Jahyeon's husband, Kwak Seunghwan] [Died 19.10.16]

286
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:29,370
Oh Jahyeon's husband.

287
00:19:30,310 --> 00:19:31,820
[Oh Jahyeon's regular OB-GYN]
[Died 19.10.19]

288
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:32,120
Oh Jahyeon's regular OB-GYN.

289
00:19:32,770 --> 00:19:34,470
[Koryoin Kim] [Died 26.01.07]

290
00:19:32,960 --> 00:19:34,960
The same kind of drugs as Oh Jahyeon.

291
00:19:36,330 --> 00:19:37,630
The casino director.

292
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,140
[Casino director]

293
00:19:39,870 --> 00:19:41,110
Oh Jahyeon.

294
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,910
It seems these 3 cases
are all related to Oh Jahyeon.

295
00:19:46,090 --> 00:19:47,360
Three cases?

296
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:49,600
Isn't there 1 more?

297
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,660
A murder case

298
00:19:52,340 --> 00:19:55,240
related to an awl and the casino.

299
00:19:56,750 --> 00:20:00,620
The starting point of all these cases.

300
00:20:03,770 --> 00:20:06,040
[Kang Woosung] [Died 11.01.21]

301
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:07,620
The murder of casino boss
Kang Woosung with an awl.

302
00:20:06,050 --> 00:20:08,050
[1 million won check found in Lee Gilyoung's house
-Stolen? Or a reward?]

303
00:20:08,220 --> 00:20:12,600
The killer was a high school classmate
of Oh Jahyeon and Kang Woosung.

304
00:20:22,970 --> 00:20:25,040
[Lee Gilyoung]

305
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:28,430
The Lee Gilyoung case...

306
00:20:29,050 --> 00:20:30,390
Are you ready?

307
00:20:33,930 --> 00:20:35,070
Yeah.

308
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:54,730
That day at Kang Woosung's house,

309
00:20:54,730 --> 00:20:56,450
his son was sleeping.

310
00:20:56,660 --> 00:20:58,320
He was a senior in high school.

311
00:20:58,770 --> 00:21:00,110
According to his statement,
he was a light sleeper

312
00:21:00,110 --> 00:21:04,010
and heard the door opening and closing—

313
00:21:04,320 --> 00:21:05,690
4 times in total.

314
00:21:06,610 --> 00:21:09,050
And the sound of the passcode lock
being pressed—

315
00:21:09,050 --> 00:21:10,120
2 times.

316
00:21:15,930 --> 00:21:19,030
I'm not drunk. I'm not.

317
00:21:21,510 --> 00:21:23,240
-You're drunk.
-I'm not drunk.

318
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:24,290
One more drink.

319
00:21:24,410 --> 00:21:26,370
Hey, wait, wait. One more drink.

320
00:21:28,050 --> 00:21:29,220
Hey.

321
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:32,830
Why drink so much
when you can't hold your liquor?

322
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:37,560
Thanks for the bonus.

323
00:21:38,180 --> 00:21:39,310
Get some rest.

324
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:40,660
I'm leaving.

325
00:21:40,820 --> 00:21:42,020
I'm not drunk.

326
00:21:52,900 --> 00:21:54,080
The first 2 sounds of the door
opening and closing

327
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:56,280
and the first sound of the passcode lock

328
00:21:56,500 --> 00:21:57,840
were probably Lee Gilyoung
bringing his boss, Kang Woosung,

329
00:21:57,840 --> 00:22:00,270
home and then leaving.

330
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:03,240
And the second sound
of the passcode lock and

331
00:22:04,470 --> 00:22:07,270
the third sound of the door
opening and closing...

332
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:11,230
Was the killer entering the passcode
to enter the house.

333
00:22:11,230 --> 00:22:12,340
Right.

334
00:22:13,210 --> 00:22:14,270
And other than his family,

335
00:22:14,270 --> 00:22:16,730
the only person who knew
the passcode was...

336
00:22:17,820 --> 00:22:20,190
His driver, Lee Gilyoung.

337
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:24,440
The reason the son, who was home
all along, didn't hear his father scream

338
00:22:47,030 --> 00:22:49,490
is because the killer
attacked from behind.

339
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:52,460
Kang Woosung didn't even
have the chance to scream.

340
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:57,900
They knew each other.

341
00:22:58,450 --> 00:23:01,070
Even though the killer
used the passcode to enter the house,

342
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:02,270
they knew each other,

343
00:23:02,370 --> 00:23:04,740
which is why Kang Woosung
didn't put up a fight.

344
00:23:04,740 --> 00:23:06,350
The first strike pierced his neck,

345
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:07,980
but it continued.

346
00:23:08,350 --> 00:23:09,250
One time.

347
00:23:10,570 --> 00:23:11,670
Two times.

348
00:23:12,330 --> 00:23:13,610
Three times.

349
00:23:14,330 --> 00:23:15,520
Four times.

350
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,730
He was stabbed

351
00:23:21,980 --> 00:23:23,530
15 more times.

352
00:23:24,130 --> 00:23:25,410
Overkill.

353
00:23:25,930 --> 00:23:27,240
A vendetta.

354
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:37,770
Did the killer really use this?

355
00:23:38,120 --> 00:23:41,810
Could it be like Granny Park's case,
where the murder weapon was switched?

356
00:23:41,810 --> 00:23:43,470
There's no way to verify that.

357
00:23:43,620 --> 00:23:46,100
There's no documented evidence
of the size and marks

358
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:47,830
of Kang Woosung's stab wounds.

359
00:23:48,140 --> 00:23:50,980
Do you think this was
an accident or intentional?

360
00:23:51,890 --> 00:23:53,630
I'm not sure.

361
00:23:55,490 --> 00:23:57,520
But one thing is certain.

362
00:24:05,030 --> 00:24:07,970
Lee Gilyoung's DNA was found on this.

363
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:10,930
But you saw Han Soojin's case.

364
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:13,600
If someone wants to,
forging this kind of evidence is nothing.

365
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:17,450
Lee Chaeha, we're not here
to prove Lee Gilyoung's innocence.

366
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:19,760
As a prosecutor and an investigator,

367
00:24:19,820 --> 00:24:23,550
we're just reviewing
one of the many related cases.

368
00:24:24,170 --> 00:24:26,580
Yes, I understand.

369
00:24:27,130 --> 00:24:30,900
I'm also talking about possibilities
based on past cases.

370
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:32,880
Okay.

371
00:24:47,610 --> 00:24:49,650
Since it's not the real murder weapon,

372
00:24:49,650 --> 00:24:51,480
it was left here so blatantly—

373
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,340
why is that?

374
00:24:53,650 --> 00:24:56,490
"I killed him. Come catch me."

375
00:24:56,710 --> 00:24:58,510
Is it a provocation, or is it...

376
00:24:59,200 --> 00:25:00,640
A signature?

377
00:25:01,570 --> 00:25:02,650
A signature?

378
00:25:02,760 --> 00:25:05,570
What if we assume
this is a serial killing?

379
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:08,770
Even though the killer
hid the real murder weapon,

380
00:25:08,770 --> 00:25:10,300
he still wanted to show off.

381
00:25:10,630 --> 00:25:12,860
"Look at me. I did this."

382
00:25:13,220 --> 00:25:15,150
If that's true,

383
00:25:15,380 --> 00:25:18,750
then the killer must still have
the awl used for the murder,

384
00:25:19,310 --> 00:25:22,540
keeping it as a souvenir
for a sick sense of superiority.

385
00:25:23,150 --> 00:25:26,740
Prosecutor Ju,
let me go see Kang Woosung's son.

386
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:30,160
Why would you go see him?

387
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:32,160
Are you going to tell him,

388
00:25:32,270 --> 00:25:35,200
"I'm the son of Lee Gilyoung
who killed your father"?

389
00:25:35,530 --> 00:25:37,170
As an investigator.

390
00:25:37,670 --> 00:25:40,750
Whether you reveal
your true identity or not,

391
00:25:41,230 --> 00:25:42,800
it's mocking to him.

392
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:47,220
After all, he'd probably want to kill you
the moment he sees you.

393
00:25:48,340 --> 00:25:49,770
I'm sorry.

394
00:25:50,010 --> 00:25:51,810
There's no need to apologize.

395
00:25:52,620 --> 00:25:56,240
What's written in the statement
should be everything.

396
00:25:56,740 --> 00:26:01,090
He couldn't even speak properly
due to the shock.

397
00:26:01,490 --> 00:26:03,000
He couldn't remember anything

398
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:04,670
for a while.

399
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:06,660
Yes.

400
00:26:11,470 --> 00:26:13,180
[Casino director]

401
00:26:12,310 --> 00:26:15,370
Do you really think Oh Jahyeon
is involved in this case?

402
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:17,610
She must be connected in some way.

403
00:26:17,770 --> 00:26:20,170
Ever since she was kicked out of Ohsong,

404
00:26:20,300 --> 00:26:25,070
she's been trying everything to get
her hands on the casino hotel project.

405
00:26:25,700 --> 00:26:26,680
But...

406
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:28,220
[Kang Woosung]

407
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:30,720
she hit a wall with Kang Woosung.

408
00:26:34,940 --> 00:26:36,340
20 billion.

409
00:26:36,580 --> 00:26:40,540
That's the profit Ohsong could make
from the hotel bidding.

410
00:26:41,010 --> 00:26:42,560
Although she couldn't return to Ohsong,

411
00:26:42,560 --> 00:26:45,790
she got the position of casino director.

412
00:26:49,130 --> 00:26:50,860
Whether as an investigator

413
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:52,930
or as Lee Gilyoung's son,

414
00:26:53,070 --> 00:26:56,460
there are 2 things to solve
to prove Lee Gilyoung's innocence.

415
00:26:56,460 --> 00:26:58,430
The sound of the door passcode, and

416
00:26:58,830 --> 00:26:59,990
the DNA.

417
00:27:07,820 --> 00:27:09,250
It's the National Forensic Service.

418
00:27:09,250 --> 00:27:10,940
I asked them to compare the DNA
on the glove

419
00:27:10,940 --> 00:27:12,550
with Director Tak's DNA.

420
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:13,650
Answer it.

421
00:27:16,570 --> 00:27:18,960
Hello, this is Supervisor Lee Chaeha.

422
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:21,100
What?

423
00:27:22,060 --> 00:27:23,140
It doesn't match?

424
00:27:23,330 --> 00:27:26,170
Right. The DNA results don't match.

425
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:28,050
However...

426
00:27:30,070 --> 00:27:31,520
Got it.

427
00:27:31,780 --> 00:27:32,820
Thank you.

428
00:27:33,140 --> 00:27:35,300
I'll contact you again.

429
00:27:36,220 --> 00:27:37,240
What's wrong?

430
00:27:37,470 --> 00:27:38,730
What did they say?

431
00:27:39,220 --> 00:27:41,260
They said it's a father-son relationship—

432
00:27:41,260 --> 00:27:44,340
between Director Tak
and the DNA detected on the glove.

433
00:27:45,020 --> 00:27:47,420
Director Tak's child...

434
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:48,960
He has a son.

435
00:27:52,370 --> 00:27:54,870
Did he drag his son in to kill someone?

436
00:27:55,490 --> 00:27:56,550
No.

437
00:27:57,030 --> 00:28:00,650
That child's DNA
couldn't possibly match his.

438
00:28:01,270 --> 00:28:04,120
That child is
from his wife's previous marriage.

439
00:28:07,020 --> 00:28:11,870
She had a boyfriend
she dated since high school.

440
00:28:12,100 --> 00:28:14,620
She got pregnant in her 20s,
but later had an abortion.

441
00:28:14,620 --> 00:28:17,510
No matter how my dad tried
to break them up, it didn't work.

442
00:28:17,510 --> 00:28:19,660
He has a son he hid.

443
00:28:20,510 --> 00:28:22,750
A son he hid?

444
00:28:23,110 --> 00:28:24,710
They have a son—

445
00:28:25,010 --> 00:28:27,940
Oh Jahyeon and Tak Sungwoong.

446
00:28:38,070 --> 00:28:40,190
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

447
00:28:40,200 --> 00:28:43,510
[Next Episode]

448
00:28:40,540 --> 00:28:43,710
Should we go to your dorm today?

449
00:28:43,870 --> 00:28:45,600
Isn't the soundproofing there quite bad?

450
00:28:45,600 --> 00:28:46,610
Yeah.

451
00:28:47,310 --> 00:28:48,370
Are you two dating?

452
00:28:48,490 --> 00:28:49,500
Huh?

453
00:28:49,780 --> 00:28:50,880
What's going on, Mr. Lee?

454
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:51,940
Are you having an office romance?

455
00:28:51,940 --> 00:28:52,950
With whom?

456
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:55,360
You said you hated office romances
the most.

457
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:56,110
Are you two-timing?

458
00:28:56,110 --> 00:28:56,870
When did I...

459
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:59,670
Oh Jahyeon and Tak Sungwoong have a son.

460
00:28:59,940 --> 00:29:04,360
I'll give each of you one secret
that you're keeping from each other.

461
00:29:04,500 --> 00:29:07,470
Lee Chaeha is Lee Gilyoung's son.

462
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:11,030
Then whose son could he be?

